manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Organyc: Complete Protection, No Compromises. Organyc brand tampons are made with 100% certified organic cotton inside & out, to give you unsurpassed absorbency and leak protection. Soft & gentle organic cotton is pure, to respect you & your body.

Organyc Cotton Tampons with a Natural Plant-Based Applicator 100% Certified Organic Cotton Organyc uses patented technology to create certified organic cotton pads, panty liners and tampons that naturally absorb as well as synthetic materials used by other brands. Our tampons have been tested and were shown to absorb as well as the traditional brands! With Organyc, you can choose the brand that offers complete protection with no compromises on purity or quality. These normal flow tampons are breathable and hypoallergenic, with no chlorine bleach, latex, parabens, perfumes, SAP, plastics or man-made materials. Our applicator is made with 90% plant-based ingredients for protection free from irritation and discomfort. Organyc brand Compact Applicator tampons are made to be inserted smoothly and comfortable to wear. Pure Organyc is Your Answer to Reactions from Ordinary Non-Cotton Products Two-thirds of women in the U.S. experience sensitive skin issues. Organyc brand tampons are made with 100% certified organic cotton and are skin pH balanced for complete comfort. Other feminine care products can have bleach and other chemicals that can be harsh on skin. Our 100% organic cotton is pure, soft, and absorbent, the way nature made it. Organyc respects you and what your body needs. Organyc is designed to respect a woman’s sensitive skin 100% certified organic cotton Unsurpassed absorbency Soft and gentle against your skin pH balanced for sensitive skin, with no chlorine bleach, latex, parabens, SAP, or man-made materials

Certified Organic Cotton for You and the Environment Our organic cotton is grown using methods and materials with the purpose of reducing the impact on the environment. Organyc proudly displays the 100% cotton seal— in fact, even our packaging is made from recycled material. Respect for the healthy lifestyle you want to lead and respect for our environment is something we take seriously. There is no organic standard for feminine care products, but our organic cotton products have been absorbed into the organic textile category. Our 100% organic cotton is certified by Global Organic Textile Standards, the leading organization for organic textiles (GOTS 2007-005 Ed.03C/Rev.00, Version 5.0, 01.03.2019).

Organyc Brand Certified Organic Cotton Products of All Kinds Organyc is proud to offer a complete range of 100% certified organic products for a range of needs from cotton rounds, to feminine pads, to beauty care. Respect for you, your skin and your needs are the essence of the Organyc brand. Key Features: · Organyc brand tampons for complete protection · Organic cotton tampons with unsurpassed absorbency · Made with no chlorine bleach, no latex, no parabens, no perfumes, no SAP, and no plastics or man-made materials · Organic feminine hygiene product for regular daytime use · 100% pure organic cotton certified by Global Organic Textile Standards (GOTS 2007-005 Ed.03C/Rev.00, Version 5.0, 01.03.2019) · For women with sensitive skin or reactions to traditional non-cotton feminine care products

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 10, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Absorbent and perfectly easy to use...
reviews.reviewText: I've been using these for literally years and I happened to notice the review section the other day, so I just felt the need to throw my support behind this product as it's always been an excellent one for me. I've personally not had issues with leaking unless I wait too long to change one, and I have ridiculously heavy periods. I recently started wearing bamboo period underwear (also from Amazon) with them just for added protection for when I'm unable to stop and get to a restroom, and while they weren't really necessary they really help with peace of mind. I don't think they're difficult to use, nor do they pinch (never had that happen to me at least) - not the plastic ones, anyway. I tried to go down that road with cardboard but I find cardboard applicators impossible and really messy.Before I used these, I used to have UTIs and yeast infections constantly. Someone asked me if I'd ever tried switching to organic tampons, because regular cotton is grown with a lot of pesticides and other stuff that can irritate sensitive vaginal tissue. I made the switch to organic and the difference was night and day. The few times I've had to use a regular tampon since, I could literally feel it burning my skin. I had probably just become so used to the irritation before that I never even noticed it. I've tried several brands of organic tampons but have always come back to these since finding them. They feel and perform, in my opinion, indistinguishably from regular tampons.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 13, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Last time I had a jar of seamoss delivered it was all busted up☹️! Today it was packed in a foam box within a cardboard box with other products. 😁 Very Happy💯

My boyfriend got these for me after he noticed a pattern of heaches, cramps and missed work around the time.. he thinks it was something to do with glysophate from non organic cotton and possibly toxic shock..Well, I get heaches and miss work much less frequently, and generally feel better around that time of the month.Great product, does what its supposed to without the extra heachey and ill feeling I would experience using more commercial products.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on August 28, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I have a high/heavy flow because of fibroids, I have always used Tampax pearl compak super plus alongside using a sanitary towel, changing frequently. I wanted to have something kind and less likely to irritate me. This did not stand up to my flow at all, I noted that others have said good absorbancy without stating their level of flow! I purchased the super plus for super heavy flow this tampon was unable to hold the flow and leaked a lot, glad I tried this at home rather than being out and about. I cannot recommend for this reason.

Der Tampon und der Applikator sind wie von O.b. Also eine super Alternative. Nur der Preis schreckt ab....Wegen dem Preis bin ich am überlegen, ob ich sie mir ein zweites Mal bestelle oder doch noch mal Tampax probiere, die ich nicht so gut finde.

reviews.reviewTitle: Once you suceed to insert, it is okay but painful to use.
reviews.reviewText: The applicator does not help anything, but rather make very painful to insert. It is terrible applicator design and too short to use as an applicator! It is impossible to push it with one hand and it stucks in the middle of the applicator so you cannot use if you fail it. You have to push the tampon a bit further before you insert and it sometimes left the cotton when you insert like that. The tampon itself is okay. It is good for heavy flow days. I wish they update the applicator.
